title: Missing person: Joan Davey, 59, of Bray Park in Brisbane | Geelong Advertiser
text:
Missing person: Joan Davey, 59, of Bray Park in Brisbane The Courier-Mail February 22, 2017 2:46pm 
A BRISBANE woman who told friends she was travelling interstate on a road trip almost two weeks ago has not been heard from since. media_camera Missing woman Joan Davey. Picture: Supplied 
Joan Davey, 59, was last seen at a residence on Pinches Crt, Bray Park, about 6am on February 10. 
Ms Davey, a keen hiker, told family and friends she intended on travelling to Boyd River, near Grafton, in NSW, but police have not been able to confirm she arrived at this destination. 
Police and family hold concerns for her welfare as she has a medical condition. 
She is described as Caucasian, about 160cm tall with a heavy build, short brown hair and blue eyes. 
She was last seen wearing outdoor clothing suitable for camping or hiking activities and was driving a blue 2012 Toyota Rav4 with Queensland registration 373SWQ. 
Phone Policelink on 131 444 or Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.
